Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: "ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'cryptography'"

Solution: Run pip3 install cryptography bcrypt or use pip3 install --user cryptography bcrypt
Issue: "Permission denied" when running scripts

Solution: Make scripts executable with chmod +x script_name.py
Issue: "Wrong master password" error when loading credentials

Solution: Ensure you're using the exact same master password. Master password is case-sensitive. If forgotten, you'll need to delete credentials.enc and salt.key to start fresh.
Issue: Import errors between modules

Solution: Ensure all Python files are in the same directory and use python3 (not python) to run scripts
